node.text: 1st place from this year's lead Czech Republic Championship on @lezeckastena.bigwall in Prague. There was definitely strange atmosphere because of the limited audience, but even though, the finals was exciting. I enjoyed the end of the route - great setting with the biggest dyno I have ever done on a lead wall. It would be pretty easy dyno on a bouldering wall, but 15 meters above the ground, it felt unnerving, for sure. Great climbing by @konecnik who took the silver, @martin.stranik was third.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Ondra on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
3rd place in Duel, 1st in combined in Rock Master 2021 👌

So the duel was definitely a little different because it was done after practice, the route was harder and it was much more about dealing with the energy and the pump ✊ So I think it was a little bit closer to the actual climbing. But in the end, I was not really expecting that we will climb faster under 1:10 and our fastest time was 1:07 in the semifinals with @michael.piccolruaz. But it was very close, but in the end, Mischa proceeded to the finals and I went on to race for the 3rd place with @yannick_flohe. That felt pretty desperate for me, my right arm was so pumped as it was the fastest to clip off the right hand for most of the clips. But I had just enough in the tank for third place.

But this year the Rock Master is the combination of boulder and duel. And thanks to first place in boulder and third place in duel I won the @rockmasterfestival for the 6th time!

Pics by @pet.phot 

#adamondra #AO #RockMaster #arco #leadclimbing #outdoorclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #climber

node.text:
1st place in Rock Master Festival Boulder! 🇮🇹

After yesterday’s practice, I think that the route setters thought that the boulders are way too easy, and they made all the boulder problems, except for the last one, significantly harder 🤯 The first one being physically turned into super physical. The boulder number two was changed with almost every hold and foothold being slightly worse that made the top almost impossible. Number three was a slab, and we barely did a move. But the number fourth was just the same as during practice, I did just on the limit, and it was incredible to top it out on my first try, being the only climber to do so and taking first place. I am happy for @martin.stranik, who took second place 💪

KO Boulder – Men

1. Adam Ondra (CZE), 2. Martin Stranik (CZE), 3. Filip Schenk (ITA), 4. Yannik Flohè (GER), 5. Michael Piccolruaz (ITA), 6. Domen Skofic (SLO), 6. Stefano Ghisolfi (ITA), 6. Ludovico Fossali (ITA)

Check out more 👉 www.rockmasterfestival.com

Pics by @pet.phot 

#adamondra #AO #rockmaster #rockmasterfestival #arco #bouldering #outdoorclimbing #boulder #boulderproblems #climber #italy

node.text:
The first day of the @rockmasterfestival - a common practice of 4 competition boulderproblems. Tomorrow only 3 tries for each problem. 

The Rock Master is a unique competition in many ways, but one of the differences is that you have some time to practice. So today was the practice day. We have practised 4 boulder problems and duel route. And, actually, it was 1-hour of practice boulderproblems and a 1-hour training duel route which was quite tiring. On duel route, we hade twice 6 minutes and within due those 6 minutes we could do whatever we wanted, so in the second 6 minutes time frame I actually I climbed route twice, and It was quite exhausting. But I definitely really looking forward to the competition.

Watch how it turned out in 2019. The link is in BIO. 

Pics by @janvogl_coto_kameruje and @pan_verner 

#adamondra #AO #rockmaster #outdoorclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #arco #arcoitaly #climbing

node.text:
After the Olympics, I am not very motivated to go to the competitions, but 🇮🇹 Arco @rockmasterfestival is not just a random contest. It is the climbing battle with the longest history in the world and I cannot miss it! ⛰️ This year the organizers will present a new format inspired by Paris 2024 - combined Boulder KO event and Duel! I cannot wait to climb on Friday, also with my compatriots @martin.stranik and @ella_adamovska 💪

Check out the latest contest from Arco in 2019 👉 the link is in BIO.

#adamondra #AO #RockMaster #Arco #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #outdoorclimbing #outdoorbouldering #italy #rockclimber #rockmasterfestival

node.text:
While training in the gym in the last months, I was definitely missing a bit of adventure 🙏 Stepping into the unknown, getting a little scared. Last weekend it was so refreshing to climb on Czech (Bohemian) sandstone again. There are special ethical rules on our sandstone like putting up routes ground up, scarce use of bolts, extra protection only by slings and knots (no metal removable gear) and no use of chalk ⛰ There are numerous crags with various rock quality, with an insane number of routes in each crag. Some places have a reputation of having bad rock and big runouts and see very little traffic. A great example is Klokočí, a home crag of Petr "Špek" Slanina, where he has put up hundreds of first ascents. A person who has probably the fattest (=strongest) fingers I have ever seen.😅 It was just amazing to climb some of his adventurous routes with him, talk just loads of shit about climbing and nothing about climbing. How much I have missed this!

The grades of these routes range between IXa and Xa of sandstone grades, which translates to 6c+ - 7c in french grading, but french grading does not really make much justice to the real difficulty of these climbs. How would you rate a final mantle onto the bushes of blueberries, risking 20m fall? 🤜🤛

Great pics by @jan.simanek

#adamondra #AO #rockclimbing #rockclimber #petrslanina #jansimanek #klokocskeskaly #czech #climbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #sandstoneclimbing #sandstoneclimb

node.text:
I really enjoyed Sunday's Olympic Festival in my hometown Brno (Czech Republic) 👌 Even though I didn't bring the medal you all wanted to see, I was really surprised by all of you who came and also delighted by the number of little athletes. I bet that I met at least 5 future Olympians and many future sport climbing hopes among them. But most importantly, many more future climbers will enjoy climbing to the fullest.

Thank you, it was nice, and it gave me really positive energy for the upcoming days 👏 

See you at the crag!

#adamondra #AO #sportclimbing #climbinglife #climbinginspiration #olympijsky #olympijskyfestivalbrno @olympijskytym @olympijskyfestival @olympics @lucie.safarova @eva_samkova

node.text:
We all watched the first sport climbing comp at the Olympics in history, and we are sure we all have opinions on what has happened 👊 The world has finally gotten to know another wonderful sport. Dynamic, thrilling, creative... beautiful. The one that Adam loves the most. Throughout his wonderful life journey, he has achieved several climbing milestones. But at the finals, within the same conditions for everyone, he ended up sixth in a row of the world's best climbers 💪

No doubt there are winners who rightfully deserve their prices and those who were just not that fortunate. But we hope this won't be too much of a mark to say, that it all just played out quite differently than a lot of us would ever think.

But you can’t outsmart the math, and in the end, it’s just a sport. There will always be somebody stronger, better prepared and yes, without even slightly degrading anybody’s performance having just that little bit more luck on his side 🏆 There will be another comps and another Olympics. All that is left to be said is this: a massive congratulation to @albertogines_, @nathaniel.coleman and @jakob.schubert for their medals. The same level of respect to all who made it to the 🇯🇵 games. 

It is a lifetime achievement. See you at the crag.

Check out the full final Tokyo Echo on the website 👉 www.adamondra.com/updates/math (the link is in BIO)

Pics by @pet.phot 

Disclaimer: During the OG all the Tokyo Echoes news is brought to you by Adam team members. Thank you very much for understanding.

Adam & AOP team

#adamondra #AO #olympics #tokyo2020 #sportclimbing #climbinginspiration #climbinglife @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
For the first time in history, the Olympic Games became the venue of a sport climbing competition 👊 20 climbers from all over the world tried to qualify for the 8-person finals in Tokyo. In 3 different categories at the same time. Speed climbing, bouldering and lead climbing. Try to imagine a legendary Usain Bolt competing in the 100 m sprint, the marathon run and the 400 m hurdles within the same day! The result we all could witness was a real qualifight 🇯🇵

The men's finals will start on Thursday, August 5 at 10:30 CET

Check out how it turned out in the new Tokyo Echo 👉 the link is in BIO. 

Great pics by @pet.phot 

CZ: 

Poprvé v historii se olympijské hry staly dějištěm záovodů ve sportovním lezení 👊 20 lezců z celého světa se v Tokiu snažilo kvalifikovat do 8členného finále. Ve 3 rozdílných kategoriích. Lezení na rychlost, bouldering a lezení na obtížnost. Zkuste si představit, že by legendární Usain Bolt závodil ve sprintu na 100 metrů, v maratonském běhu a v disciplíně 400 m překážek v rámci jednoho dne! Výsledek, kterého jsme všichni mohli být svědky, byl skutečný kvalifikační boj 🇯🇵

Podívejte se, jak to nakonec dopadlo v nové Ozvěně z Tokia 👉 link na anglický článek najdete v BIO profilu. 

Finále mužů začíná už zítra v 10:30 našeho času. 

Skvělé fotky od @pet.phot 

#adamondra #AO #sportclimbing #climbing #olympics #tokyo2020 #climbinginspiration #climbinglife @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
We bet you will enjoy this progressive format as much as we do. @nytimes has created an impressive form of interactive Olympic articles to bring people closer to athletes, their skills, strength and challenges 💪 

In the one devoted to Adam, more than 24 journalists and graphics, including @wardnyt skilfully covered all the 3 climbing events that Adam will go through this year — speed, lead and boulder climbing 👌 Using special cameras to capture how Adam climbs in 3-D, infographics, videos and short batched comments, NYT deconstructed and analysed Adam’s moves and created quite a jazzed up story of it all. 

You can experience the article through what is called augmented reality (you will need the Instagram app), and some of the climbing moves are even labelled so you can easily tap into climbing terminology.

Check out the full interactive piece 👉 the link is in BIO. The fifth link from the top in the link beta. 

Many thanks, @wardnyt and the @nytimes team!

Disclaimer: During the OG Adam will be solely focusing on his physical and mental preparations for the finals. Therefore all the Tokyo Echoes news is brought to you by his team members. Thank you very much for understanding 🙏

AOP Team

#adamondra #AO #nytimes #interactivepiece #bouldering #sportclimbing #climbing #speedclimbing #climber #climbinginspiration #climbinglife #joeward

node.text:
A lot of you asked how Adam trains for competitions. So we asked two 🇨🇿 Czech top athletes from different sports to find it out for you 👌

Thanks to @eva_samkova, the Olympic medalist from snowboard cross, and @zhejnova, the Olympic medalist from 400 metres hurdles, for taking part in this little Olympic talk! 💪 Link to the full video in BIO.

AOP Team

#adamondra #AO #sportclimbing #climbinginspiration #tokyo2020 #olympijsky #olympics @olympijskytym @olympics @tokyo2020

node.text:
Adam has successfully arrived in Tokyo and he is already acclimatising with the other athletes in the village. Probably thanks to Pavel's (Adam's physiotherapist) recovery techniques, Adam says he feels "suspiciously good" and it seems like he left the jet leg on the plane this time 😎

Wondering when Adam's first training session is and what time the men's qualification starts? Check out the full current Tokyo Echo on the website 👉 the link is in BIO (the second link)

Disclaimer: During the OG Adam will be solely focusing on his physical and mental preparations for the finals. Therefore all the Tokyo Echoes news is brought to you by his team members. Thank you very much for understanding.
